  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "We observe missing values in several variables. annotatorAge has 23 missing values and importance has 144 missing values, which are relatively small compared to the total dataset size. However, frequency (2756 missing) and similarity (4098 missing) contain substantial missingness. Since these are self reported ratings, the missingness may be related to other observed characteristics rather than occurring completely at random. Rather than making strong assumptions about the missingness mechanism, we handle these variables cautiously by imputing low missingness columns and using available observations for exploratory analyses involving frequency or similarity."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Imputation\n",
    "\n",
    "Since annotatorAge and importance contain relatively small amounts of missing data compared to the total dataset size, we use mode imputation to fill these missing values. Mode imputation replaces missing entries with the most common value in the column, which is appropriate for ordinal or categorical variables like age buckets and Likert scale ratings. This allows us to retain nearly all observations without introducing large distortions in the distribution.\n",
    "\n",
    "However, we do not apply imputation to frequency or similarity because these variables contain substantial missingness. Instead, when analyzing these variables, we restrict the analysis to rows where the values are observed."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 8,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "0"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 8,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "mode_age = hippo['annotatorAge'].mode(dropna=True)[0]\n",
    "hippo['annotatorAge'] = hippo['annotatorAge'].fillna(mode_age)\n",
    "hippo['annotatorAge'].isna().sum()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 9,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
