   "source": [
    "We notice here that the distribution of responses for stress, drain, and distraction all follow a right-skewed distribution. Meaning that most people responded with a less 'extreme' storytelling experience, but with groups of people spread out with more extreme responses to recalling their story, which is pulling the mean of each distribution to the right. \n",
    "\n",
    "### Word Count\n",
    "since word count of the stories will be important to us, and is not already in the dataset, we can add it ourselves."
