    "sns.regplot(\n",
    "    data=hippo,\n",
    "    x='word_count',\n",
    "    y='log_worktime',\n",
    "    scatter_kws={'alpha':0.2, 's':15},\n",
    "    lowess=True,\n",
    "    line_kws={'color':'black'}\n",
    ")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "The scatter plot compares story length with the log-transformed total task time, with a LOWESS trend line showing the general relationship between the two variables. The trend line indicates a slight positive relationship, where longer stories tend to correspond with somewhat higher completion times. However, the increase is gradual, and the large vertical spread of points at most word counts shows that total task time varies widely even for stories of similar length. This suggests that while writing longer stories generally requires more time, other factors such as recalling the event or thinking before writing also contribute to the total effort required."
   ]
