    "## EDA Section 2 Summary\n",
    "Overall, the exploratory analysis shows that recall of emotional memories is heavily right-skewed. Between the duration of recall with emotions, “happy” cue words and “sad” cue words do not have a significant difference between their medians. This indicates that the type of emotion (positive/negative) experienced by the participants when recalling memories may not affect the duration of their recall. The difference between the histograms show the difference in emotion when recalling an event vs. actually experiencing the event. The scatterplots show no significant patterns, where the sentiment score (used to quantify emotion tone) is plot alongside memory duration (used to quantify detail in recall). Overall, these patterns reveal that valence (past/present) may have an effect on memory recall duration and detail."
